== 11...g5 · Morozevich variation ==
11...g5 is the most popular line nowadays and is considered the best move for Black. Because the kingside pawn structure is significantly weakened, Black will usually resort to castling queenside.

'''12. Bxg5??''' would blunder 12...Nxc4. The bishop can't stay on the same diagonal as the black queen, so some pieces have to be traded. 

[[/12. Bxe5|'''12. Bxe5''']] allows Black to secure the bishop pair after 12...Nxe5 but White gets compensation after '''13. Qd4 f6 14. O-O-O''' preventing Black from castling queenside.

[[/12. Ne3|'''12. Ne3''']] is played most often, planning to take the light-squared bishop. After '''12...gxf4 13. Nxf5 O-O-O 14. Qc2''' Black has two isolated pawns on the kingside, but a four on two majority on the queenside and has control of the d-file. White should soon castle short.

=== History ===
The Morozevich is named after the player Alexander Morozevich, who was the first person to play the variation and did so against Garry Kasparov in the year 2000<ref>https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessgame?gid=1005706</ref>.

